# ============================================================
# ITEM CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: item
scope: item.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for item.

## policy_rules
Item policy constrains:
- who may view which item details
- who may possess/use/transfer items
- what item states may be disclosed
- when item paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- possession scope must be explicit
- use/transfer scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public item summary
- holder-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical item detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow possession/use/transfer only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden authority widening through possession
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If item identity,
possession scope,
use/transfer scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the item path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- possession policy is explicit
- use/transfer policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
